independence /ˌɪndɪˈpɛndəns/

1. N-UNCOUNT If a country has or gains independence , it has its own government and is not ruled by any other country. (国家的) 独立 

例： In 1816, Argentina declared its independence from Spain. 1816年，阿根廷宣布脱离西班牙而独立。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Someone's independence is the fact that they do not rely on other people. (人的) 自立 

例： He was afraid of losing his independence. 他担心丧失自己的独立。

</div>

